.TH GEN-README "1" "December 2025" "gen-readme 202208082241-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
gen-readme \- README file generator from templates
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gen-readme
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,COMMAND\/\fR] [\fI\,ARGUMENTS\/\fR]
.br
.B gen-readme
[\fI\,TEMPLATE\/\fR] [\fI\,OUTPUT_FILE\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B gen-readme
is a README file generator that creates README.md files for software projects using customizable templates. It automatically substitutes variables for project name, author, description, version, and other metadata.
.PP
The script supports template management from local files or remote git repositories, searches for templates by category, and can extract project descriptions from existing scripts. Templates can be customized and stored locally for repeated use.
.PP
gen-readme is designed for developers who need consistent README files across multiple projects with automatic variable substitution.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B gen-readme [template] [output]
Create a README.md file using the specified template (default: default.md)
.TP
.B gen-readme list
List all available README templates from the templates directory
.TP
.B gen-readme search [pattern]
Search for README templates matching the specified pattern
.TP
.B gen-readme download [repo_url]
Download README templates from the configured git repository
.TP
.B gen-readme custom [file/url]
Use a custom template file from local path or remote URL
.TP
.B gen-readme all [template] [output]
Alias for the default template generation behavior
.TP
.B gen-readme man [name] [template]
Generate a man page template using pandoc
