.SH CONFIGURATION FILE
The configuration file located at ~/.config/myscripts/gen-readme/settings.conf supports the following settings:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
GEN_README_FILE_DIR="$HOME/.config/myscripts/gen-readme/files"
GEN_README_DEFAULT_TEMPLATE="default.md"
GEN_README_DEFAULT_USER="Your Name"
GEN_README_REGISTRY_USER="dockerhubuser"
GEN_README_GIT_EMAIL="you@example.com"
GEN_README_GIT_BRANCH="main"
GEN_README_FILES_REPO="https://github.com/devenvmgr/readmes"
GEN_README_NOTIFY_ENABLED="yes"
.EE
.RE
.SH TEMPLATE VARIABLES
Template files support variable substitution. The following placeholders are replaced during file generation:
.PP
.TS
tab(;);
l l.
Placeholder;Replaced With
_
REPLACE_USER;Author name (GEN_README_DEFAULT_USER)
REPLACE_APPNAME;Application/directory name
REPLACE_AUTHOR_NAME;Author name
REPLACE_PROJECT_NAME;Project name
REPLACE_DEFAULT_BRANCH;Git default branch (main)
REPLACE_REGISTRY_USER;Docker registry username
REPLACE_DESCRIBE;Project description (from install.sh or custom)
REPLACE_VERSION;Version timestamp
.TE
.SH TEMPLATE DIRECTORY STRUCTURE
Templates can be organized in subdirectories for different project types:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
~/.config/myscripts/gen-readme/files/
├── default.md              # Default template
├── dockermgr/
│   └── default.md          # Docker project template
├── dfmgr/
│   └── default.md          # Dotfiles template
├── iconmgr/
│   └── default.md          # Icon theme template
└── systemmgr/
    └── default.md          # System tool template
.EE
.RE
.PP
Access templates using path: gen-readme dockermgr/default
